 President Muhammadu Buhari is currently meeting with All Progressive Congress (APC) governors in the Presidential Villa. The meeting which is holding at the Council Chambers of the State House is also being attended by Abdullahi Adamu, the party’s National Chairman of the Party. Also in attendance are Boss Mustapha, Secretary to the Government of the Federation, Ibrahim Gambari of Staff of the President. Read also: Buhari urges states to domesticate child rights act Governors of the All Progressive Congress are in attendance with the exception of Kaduna who is being represented by his deputy, Hadiza Balarabe. The meeting is coming on the heels of the ongoing screening of the APC presidential aspirants ahead of the primary election earlier scheduled for June 6-8. The meeting, BusinessDay, gathered is crucial as it is being used to strategize ahead of the presidential primary, as the President is expected to proceed to Spain, after today’s meeting